Place sugar in bowl of food processor fitted with metal blade; pulse 20 seconds. Add watermelon and puree until smooth. Pour into shallow glass baking dish (11x7 or 13x9-inches). Stir in juice. Freeze 4 to 6 hours or until firm. Scrape and mash with tines of fork to form fluffy crystals. Spoon into chilled wine glasses or bowls. Serve at once.